sec.p:
Inclusion criteria for participation are as follows:
being part of a couple of opposite biological sex;
incident referral for the couple (the partners may have been examined or treated individually before);
referral for infertility investigation or fertility treatment;
age (depending on national regulations):
women: age 18–41 years in Denmark and 24–39 years in Sweden;
men: 18 years or older in Denmark (no upper age limit) and 24–53 years in Sweden.

Exclusion criteria for participation are as follows:
inability to understand study information given in Danish or Swedish;
surgical sterilization;
HIV or hepatitis A, B, or C.
